{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"922fad2a-3e36-4564-8352-30c601c4d412","content":"\n\nHere's a quick overview of common web API templates and auth options:\n\n### .NET (`dotnet new`)\n- **`webapi`** — standard Web API template\n- Auth options (`--auth`): `None`, `IndividualB2C`, `SingleOrg`, `Windows`\n\n### Node.js / Express\n- Use `express-generator` or frameworks like **Fastify**, **NestJS**\n- Auth: **Passport.js** (JWT, OAuth2, local), **express-jwt**, or **Auth0 SDK**\n\n### Python\n- **FastAPI** or **Flask**\n- Auth: **OAuth2 with JWT** (built into FastAPI), **Flask-Login**, **Authlib**\n\n### ASP.NET Core specifics (`dotnet new webapi`)\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C   # Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg       # Azure AD (single tenant)\ndotnet new webapi -au MultiOrg           # Azure AD (multi-tenant)\n```\n\n**Recommendation:** If you're in .NET, `dotnet new webapi` with `--auth` is the fastest start. For Node/Python, pair your framework with **JWT bearer tokens** for stateless API auth.\n\nWant me to scaffold a specific project for you?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"aa7fb7c6-1c6c-48a9-b263-35fc382f63e8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common web frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the most common frameworks.","outputTokens":372},"id":"4d30e7dd-ac2e-4329-9166-333ffa2b3c04","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:52:38.117Z","parentId":"26653df4-3b74-45b9-b928-2930dc7014fb"}
